  "prompt": "Is there any law in India to secretly report child labour?",
  "response": "Yes, in India, there are mechanisms in place for reporting child labor, including provisions that allow for anonymous reporting. The Child and Adolescent Labour (Prohibition and Regulation) Act, 1986, along with the Right of Children to Free and Compulsory Education Act, 2009, aims to combat child labor and protect children's rights.\n\nAdditionally, the Ministry of Labour and Employment has launched various initiatives and helplines to report instances of child labor. For example, the National Child Labour Project (NCLP) provides a framework for addressing child labor, and individuals can report cases through this project.\n\nYou can also reach out to local NGOs, child welfare committees, or use helplines that operate in various states, which allow for complaints to be made anonymously. Reporting channels are often designed to encourage individuals to come forward without fear of repercussions, making it easier to tackle the issue of child labor discreetly.",
